      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Succinic anhydride yields the cyclic imide succinimide when heated with ammonium chloride at 200 °C. Propose a mechanism for this reaction. Why do you suppose such a high reaction temperature is required?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaWtYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e705977d3f5fbb3d1947e5ad8273984271794bef/OChem_21_EC_033.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction shows the conversion of dihydrofuran-2, 5-dione to an amide by heating at two-hundred degrees Celcius in the presence of ammonium chloride.\">",
